0mental%20fatigue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShort%20bursts%20of%20exercise%20can%20improve%20your%20health%20and%20help%20extend%20your%20life%2C%20research%20has%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20stuck%20in%20a%20midday%20slump%2C%20hitting%20a%20quick%20round%20of%20squats%20may%20help%20shake%20off%20the%20brain%20fog%2C%20new%20research%20suggests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20a%20desk%20job%20and%20other%20sedentary%20lifestyle%20habits%20are%20a%20known%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsedentary-lifestyle-associated-with-increased-risk-of-cancer-study-finds-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehealth%20hazard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contributing%20to%20higher%20risk%20of%20illnesses%20like%20cancer%2C%20heart%20disease%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nia.nih.gov%2Fnews%2Fstrong-association-shown-between-being-sedentary-and-dementia-risk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecognitive%20decline%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20research%20indicates%20that%20short%20exercise%20breaks%20can%20help%20offset%20the%20harm%2C%20both%20for%20your%20mind%20and%20your%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20minute%20(literally)%20to%20rep%20out%20some%20squats%20is%20linked%20to%20better%20blood%20flow%20to%20the%20brain%2C%20and%20better%20concentration%20and%20decision-making%20power%2C%20according%20to%20a%20small%20study%20published%20November%209%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.physiology.org%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1152%2Fjapplphysiol.00437.2023%3Futm_source%3DJAPPL%26utm_medium%3DPressRelease%26utm_campaign%3D11.29.2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJournal%20of%20Applied%20Physiology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20from%20Japan%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20studied%20a%20group%20of%2020%20young%20adults%2C%20averaging%20around%2021%20years%20old%2C%20as%20they%20completed%20mental%20tests%20after%20sitting%20for%20long%20periods%20of%20time.%20In%20one%20experiment%2C%20the%20participants%20sat%20for%20three%20hours%20uninterrupted%20before%20completing%20the%20tests%2C%20while%20in%20the%20other%2C%20they%20broke%20up%20their%20seated%20time%20with%20one-minute%20sessions%20of%20squat%20exercise%20combined%20with%20calf%20raises%2C%20for%20about%2015%20reps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20when%20participants%20took%20the%20exercise%20breaks%2C%20they%20had%20better%20executive%20function%20as%20well%20as%20faster%20reaction%20times.%20They%20also%20self-reported%20better%20concentration%20and%20less%20mental%20fatigue%20than%20when%20they%20sat%20without%20breaks.%20Measuring%20blood%20flow%20to%20the%20brain%20during%20the%20experiments%2C%20researchers%20found%20participants%20saw%20a%20decrease%20when%20they%20were%20fully%20sedentary%2C%20compared%20to%20a%20slight%20increase%20when%20they%20did%20the%20short%20exercises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20catch%20(because%20of%20course%20there%20is%20one)%20is%20that%20it%20wasn't%20a%20one-and-done%20solution%2C%20since%20the%20participants%20repeated%20the%20exercise%20every%2020%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20most%20convenient%20if%20you're%20sitting%20down%20for%20meetings%20or%20other%20work-related%20tasks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20findings%20add%20to%20previous%20research%20that%20micro-workouts%20help%20you%20to%20stay%20fit%20and%20healthy%20even%20if%20you're%20sitting%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20provide%20a%20good%20excuse%20to%20step%20away%20from%20your%20desk%20for%20productivity's%20sake%2C%20if%20only%20for%20a%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExercise%20%26quot%3Bsnacks%26quot%3B%20can%20boost%20your%20energy%2C%20health%2C%20and%20even%20longevity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBetter%20brain%20power%20isn't%20the%20only%20benefit%20from%20small%20doses%20of%20exercise%2C%20as%20several%20previous%20studies%20have%20foun