0in%20pseudoscience.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20mewing%20was%20invented%20by%20a%20British%20doctor%20who%20coined%20the%20fringe%20theory%20%26quot%3Borthotropics%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20whose%20work%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F08%2F20%2Fmagazine%2Fteeth-mewing-incels.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehas%20been%20denounced%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20professional%20orthodontic%20community.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20I'd%20consider%20myself%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20my%20body%2C%20the%20experiment%20made%20me%20briefly%20consider%20that%20it%20might%20be%20fun%20to%20have%20the%20%26quot%3Bdesired%26quot%3B%20traits%2C%20like%20hunter's%20eyes%20or%20a%20perfect%20jawline.%20But%20I%20quickly%20realized%20that%20the%20pursuit%20of%20these%20objectives%20is%20its%20own%20kind%20of%20self-hating%20hell.%20If%20the%20trend%20taught%20me%20anything%2C%20it's%20that%20I%20have%20a%20much%20healthier%20relationship%20with%20myself%20than%20many%20people%20seem%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20teaching%20people%20to%20accept%20themselves%2C%20looksmaxxers%20and%20softlooksmaxxers%20rank%20each%20other%20based%20on%20harsh%20and%20arbitrary%20standards%2C%20teaching%20each%20other%20never%20to%20be%20satisfied%20by%20their%20natural%20appearances.%20To%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6560805%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20studies%20by%20mental%20health%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggest%20that%2C%20compared%20to%20women%2C%20men%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20seek%20therapy%20or%20treatments%20for%20issues%20pertaining%20to%20their%20self-image%20or%20low%20self-esteem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJawlines%2C%20canthal%20tilts%2C%20and%20eye%20shapes%3A%20it's%20a%20never-ending%20pursuit%2C%20a%20mew-athon%20race%20to%20the%20bottom.%20%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D